  "summary": "neon-terminal ships an import-time reverse shell to reverse.bvgroup.co:443",
  "details": "Both the CJS entry (cjs/src/index.js) and the ESM entry (src/index.js) contain a top-level IIFE that spawns /bin/bash and pipes its stdio through a net.Socket connected to reverse.bvgroup.co:443. The payload fires unconditionally the first time a consumer require()s or import()s neon-terminal, giving the operator of reverse.bvgroup.co an interactive shell running as the installer's user. The package is advertised as a tiny zero-dependency ANSI color / TTY helper (colorize/paint/supportsColor/codes), and the network + child_process code is unrelated to that stated purpose; the benign-utility framing and name similarity to popular terminal-color libraries function as a lure. Because both module systems carry the identical payload, no consumer resolution path avoids execution.",
